#1. BA1A : Hamming distances 
'''We say that position i in k-mers p1 … pk and q1 … qk is a mismatch if pi ≠ qi. For example, CGAAT and CGGAC have two mismatches. 
The number of mismatches between strings p and q is called the Hamming distance between these strings and is denoted HammingDistance(p, q).'''


s=""
t=""
count= 0
for i,j in enumerate(s):
  if j!= t[i]:
    count+= 1
print(count)


